I'm assuming (it's late here, and I'm falling asleep) that you're saying:  in the SCP, I meant that the computer finished rendering the image to the level of detail it was programmed to. In-universe, that should be close enough to produce the anomalous effect.

Out-of-character, one of the things I learned while writing this is that for a mathematical SCP to work, it has to make sense to all the non-mathematicians (without them having to go look stuff up, or feeling like they are being taught math instead of reading a story). At the same time, it has to not sound like complete BS to the folks who know more about the underlying math. It's a fine line and I've probably leaned towards staying away from any overly mathematical details.








